Reply. He did rely upon them in the ſame way, as the ignorant Quaker doth: for he was one at that time; and ſo this Lord was no other than the Light within: and the inſtructions of the Lord, (that he ſpeaks of;) no other but the Dictates of Nature. No wonder he wandred: Nature will not teach the right way of Prayer: neither can
